  • Method Details

    • startAsync

      public com.solana.mobilewalletadapter.common.util.NotifyingCompletableFuture<String> startAsync()
      Description copied from interface: Scenario
      Start the scenario, asynchronously

      This method starts the connection process but returns immediately with a NotifyingCompletableFuture. The returned future will be completed once the scenario has successfully established a session.

      If session establishment fails for any reason, the Future will throw an ExecutionException with the cause of the failure.

      Specified by:
      startAsync in interface Scenario
      Overrides:
      startAsync in class LocalScenario
      Returns:
      a Future that completes with a session UUID when the session is established.
